    b"luate the conversation and produce memory search hints for\x0d\x0a        the selected"
    b" task.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        The hints will drive memory search before the selected task ru"
    b"ns.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Stop once the hints look good enough for the request without thin"
    b"king about it too much.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Search surfaces:\x0d\x0a        - tags: exact memor"
    b"y tags. They are not substring searched.\x0d\x0a        - strings.contains: case-insen"
    b"sitive text fragments. Each value is checked\x0d\x0a          as a substring against s"
    b"earchable memory content.\x0d\x0a        - strings.equals: exact text values. Each val"
    b"ue is checked for exact\x0d\x0a          equality against searchable memory content.\x0d\x0a"
    b"\x0d\x0a        Optional outputs available in this step:\x0d\x0a        - candidate_memory: "
    b"a vague remembered observation that could be useful to\x0d\x0a          preserve.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a "
    b"       Rules:\x0d\x0a        - Return only search hints and optional candidate_memory."
    b"\x0d\x0a        - Search hints are alternatives during retrieval; a memory can be usef"
